The paper discusses non-linear dimensionality reduction techniques and their application to high-dimensional data analysis. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), and signal processing (cs.SI). Given the focus on dimensionality reduction and function estimation, cs.LG and cs.CV are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.AI, cs.NE, and cs.SI.
